isitors-centric public spaces planning approach. ANDES can determine the public space and real estate values. According to Kountouriotis et al. (2014), crowd behavior models are divided into agent-based, flow-based and particle-based depending on whether the behavior appears as simulating all persons separately, is programmatically defined a priori applying a fluid dynamics models, or using a particle system subject to physical laws.Zhou et al. (2010) stated that current crowd models and simulation systems can be incompletely characterized by applying a two-dimensional taxonomy determined by crowd scope and time dimensions.
