lability of associated field notes and photographs, and deaccessioning practices (Huster, 2013; Luby et al., 2013; Voss, 2012).Despite these and other obstacles, analysis of archaeological museum collections is an important pursuit, where large collections can be analyzed on their own, or supplement new excavations at a site (Crowell, 2000; Luby et al., 2013; Rick, 2007).
