fness which is based on an analysis of shear waves induced in the liver by low-frequency vibrations applied to the abdominal wall.In cross-sectional studies, MRE has demonstrated high diagnostic accuracy for discriminating fibrosis stage and predicting clinical complications.14–17However, the correlation between change in MRE-estimated liver stiffness with histologic response is unknown, and a clinically relevant threshold for MRE-estimated liver stiffness reduction for predicting an anti-fibrotic response has not been identified.
