 it may be accompanied by severe liver injury (sALI) or acute liver failure (ALF), both of which have a poor prognosis.This liver injury is clearly due to multiple factors: lesions induced by hyperthermia, hypoxia, endotoxemia, blood coagulation disorders or sepsis.It is often one symptom of severe multiple organ dysfunction or multiple organ failure.The control of body temperature by cooling as soon as the patient is taken in charge is essential and will influence the severity of organ injury.
