, hepatic steatosis, dyslipidaemia, gradual decline in hepatic function, and premature atherosclerosis.These conditions are difficult to diagnose; it is unclear how many children die of undiagnosed WD and there is currently no consensus on routine testing for LIPA activity in adults presenting with NAFLD.
