 referred to as E8SJM,13 which has been used to derive an estimated prevalence as high as 1 per 40,000.This is much higher than clinical observations, leading to the suggestion that LAL-D is under-diagnosed and may be unmasked in patients presenting with NAFLD.3,14–16
